    <stitle>SPICER 14 INCH (350 MM) SOLO CLUTCH - INSTALL - SINGLE PLATE CLUTCH ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1100402" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="7">
        <title>SINGLE PLATE CLUTCH ASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>Follow this procedure if the shipping bolts were installed prior to removing the clutch cover
                    assembly and the same driven discs are being re-used or a factory replacement clutch and disc
                    assembly is being installed.
                </para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>In the event the shipping bolts were not installed during the removal procedure or new driven
                    discs are being installed with the existing cover assembly, the cover assembly roll pin/bolt
                    assembly must be reset following
                    <hotlnk document="s11004_HL1100403.xml" xrefid="hl1100403">RESETTING PROCEDURES</hotlnk>
                    before proceeding with Step 4.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new pilot bearing in the flywheel (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100411">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1100411" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1100411" filename="../figg11/G1100411.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Install New Pilot Bearing in Flywheel</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two 3/8" x 16 x 3" long guide studs at the 11 and 1 o'clock positions on the
                flywheel (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100412">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1100412" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1100412" filename="../figg11/G1100412.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Install Guide Studs</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the driven disc by inserting an alignment tool through the disc splines and into the
                flywheel pilot bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100413">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1100413" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1100413" filename="../figg11/G1100413.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Install Driven Disc</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the cover assembly by sliding it over the guide studs and alignment tool (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100414">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1100414" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1100414" filename="../figg11/G1100414.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Install Cover Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install (6) 3/8" x 1.412" long grade 5 min. mounting bolts and lockwashers hand tight.
                Remove the two guide studs and replace with two additional bolts and lockwashers. Tighten to 30 to 35
                ft-lbs. (41 to 47 N&#8226;m) in a criss-cross pattern (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100415">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1100415" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1100415" filename="../figg11/G1100415.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Tighten Bolts to Pattern Shown</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the (4) shipping bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100416">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1100416" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1100416" filename="../figg11/G1100416.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Remove Shipping Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If the clutch is a factory replacement, the shipping bolts will be colored yellow.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para></para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the alignment tool (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100417">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1100417" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1100417" filename="../figg11/G1100417.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Remove Alignment Tool</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
